[[File:MR-RIO-A special purpose computer developed by KB Korund-M at 2013 MAKS Airshow.JPG|thumb|MR-[[RapidIO|RIO]]-A special purpose computer developed by Korund-M at 2013 [[MAKS Airshow]]]]
'''[[OKB|KB]] Korund-M''' is a [[Russia]]n R&D production enterprise, founded in 1994 as an autonomous non-commercial organization controlled by [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] and specializing on electronic modules for severe working conditions. Also it is specializing on development and production of complex high-reliability electronic elements and computing machines.

KB is tightly connected with NPC Sapnas and KB Navis.

== Production ==
* ''Baget''-series electronic computers either on [[Intel Corporation|Intel]] [[x86 architecture|architecture]] ([[Intel 80386EX|80386EX]]/[[Intel 80486|80486EX]]) or [[MIPS Technologies|MIPS]] [[MIPS architecture|(R3000, R4000 analogues), MIPS64]], [[KOMDIV-32]], [[KOMDIV-64]]. This modules were developed for working under [[Real-time operating system|Real-time]] [[operating system]] [[VxWorks]], and its Russian analogue [[OS2000]];
* math accelerators developed on the basis of [[Motorola]] [[Digital signal processor|DSP]]96002;
* multiprocessor systems.

